<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Emperor</gloss> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rhainsburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-06"><hi rend="italic">July 6,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p rend="flushleft">The President of the United States, Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">McKinley</hi>:</p>
                            <p>For Your Excellency’s warm words of condolence in the murder of my
                                representative in Pekin I express my most sincere thanks. I
                                recognize therein the common impulse of interests which binds the
                                civilized nations together.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilhelm, R.
                                I.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>